frus:attachment.p:
“When a belligerent warship meets a merchantman on the high
                        seas which is known to be enemy-owned, and attempts to capture the vessel, the latter may exercise its right
                        of self-protection either by flight or by resistance”;

“it has become the established practice for warships to give
                        merchant vessels an opportunity to surrender or submit to visit and search
                        before attempting to seize them by force”;
